text.tspan: Primary energy consumption by world region
Primary energy consumption is measured in terawatt-hours (TWh). Note that this data includes only
commercially-traded fuels (coal, oil, gas), nuclear and modern renewables used in electricity production.
As such, it does not include traditional biomass sources.
Data source: BP Statistical Review of World Energy (2019)
